          </LEXCollocations>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-04 22:00:12" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to be baptized with a baptism) to be overwhelmed by some difficult experience or ordeal</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to suffer</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to undergo</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is usually not possible to employ the general term for ‘baptism’ to indicate a difficult trial or ordeal. On the other hand, there may be a serious problem involved in using a technical term for ‘ordeal,’ since such an expression may imply merely a ‘proof of innocence.’ In a number of languages, therefore, one can best translate the idiom simply as ‘to suffer greatly.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
